HEADWORD: Muliebrity
<hw>Mu`li*eb"ri*ty</hw> <pr>(m⟦umac⟧`l⟦icr⟧*⟦ecr⟧b"r⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>muliebritas</ets>, fr. <ets>muliebris</ets>
belonging to a woman, fr. <ets>mulier</ets> a woman.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state of being a woman or of possessing full womanly powers;
womanhood; -- correlate of <contr>virility</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Effeminancy;
softness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mulier</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
